abstract: India has offered to partially open up its poultry and dairy markets in a bid for a limited trade deal during U.S. President Donald Trump's first official visit to the country this month, people familiar with the protracted talks say.
snippet: India has offered to partially open up its poultry and dairy markets in a bid for a limited trade deal during U.S. President Donald Trump's first official visit to the country this month, people familiar with the protracted talks say.
lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI/WASHINGTON — India has offered to partially open up its poultry and dairy markets in a bid for a limited trade deal during U.S. President Donald Trump's first official visit to the country this month, people familiar with the protracted talks say.
headline_main: India Offers U.S. Dairy, Chicken Access in Bid for Elusive Trade Deal With Trump
headline_print_headline: India Offers U.S. Dairy, Chicken Access in Bid for Elusive Trade Deal With Trump

abstract: President Donald Trump's former chief of staff John Kelly has dismissed the U.S. president's unprecedented engagement with North Korean leader Kim Jong Un as futile, saying he had never believed North Korea would give up its nuclear weapons and Pyongyang had played the United States to its benefit.
snippet: President Donald Trump's former chief of staff John Kelly has dismissed the U.S. president's unprecedented engagement with North Korean leader Kim Jong Un as futile, saying he had never believed North Korea would give up its nuclear weapons and Py...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump's former chief of staff John Kelly has dismissed the U.S. president's unprecedented engagement with North Korean leader Kim Jong Un as futile, saying he had never believed North Korea would give up its nuclear weapons and Pyongyang had played the United States to its benefit.
headline_main: Former Chief of Staff Kelly Rejects Trump North Korea Approach as Futile: Report
headline_print_headline: Former Chief of Staff Kelly Rejects Trump North Korea Approach as Futile: Report

abstract: A White House meeting between U.S. President Donald Trump and New York Governor Andrew Cuomo over New York's pro-immigrant policies was "productive," according to Trump's top homeland official.
snippet: A White House meeting between U.S. President Donald Trump and New York Governor Andrew Cuomo over New York's pro-immigrant policies was "productive," according to Trump's top homeland official.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A White House meeting between U.S. President Donald Trump and New York Governor Andrew Cuomo over New York's pro-immigrant policies was "productive," according to Trump's top homeland official.
headline_main: Trump Had 'Productive' Meeting With Cuomo Over NY Immigrant Policies: Official
headline_print_headline: Trump Had 'Productive' Meeting With Cuomo Over NY Immigrant Policies: Official

abstract: New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo visited the White House on Thursday in the hope he could persuade President Donald Trump to reverse a decision to boot New Yorkers from programs that allow travelers to avoid long lines at the U.S. border.
snippet: New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo visited the White House on Thursday in the hope he could persuade President Donald Trump to reverse a decision to boot New Yorkers from programs that allow travelers to avoid long lines at the U.S. border.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo visited the White House on Thursday in the hope he could persuade President Donald Trump to reverse a decision to boot New Yorkers from programs that allow travelers to avoid long lines at the U.S. border.
headline_main: Cuomo Meets With Trump to Offer Deal on Travelers Program
headline_print_headline: Cuomo Meets With Trump to Offer Deal on Travelers Program

abstract: Virginia, newly dominated by Democrats, may broaden parole for the first time in a generation. Others states are watching.
snippet: Virginia, newly dominated by Democrats, may broaden parole for the first time in a generation. Others states are watching.
lead_paragraph: WAVERLY, Va. — After Zenas Barnes was convicted of three robberies in the 1990s, he accepted a plea deal that stunned even veteran lawyers for its severity: 150 years in state prison.

abstract: U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo on Thursday said he is “outraged” by the U.N.'s publication of a list of companies accused of violating Palestinian human rights by operating in Israel's West Bank settlements.
snippet: U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo on Thursday said he is “outraged” by the U.N.'s publication of a list of companies accused of violating Palestinian human rights by operating in Israel's West Bank settlements.
lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM — U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo on Thursday said he is “outraged” by the U.N.'s publication of a list of companies accused of violating Palestinian human rights by operating in Israel's West Bank settlements.
headline_main: Pompeo 'Outraged' by UN List of Firms With Settlement Ties
